## Notebook Resource Properties {#properties}

To learn more about resource properties and how to use them, see [Inputs and Outputs](/docs/intro/concepts/inputs-outputs) in the Architecture and Concepts docs.

### Inputs

The Notebook resource accepts the following [input](/docs/intro/concepts/inputs-outputs) properties:



<div>
<pulumi-choosable type="language" values="csharp">
<dl class="resources-properties"><dt class="property-required"
            title="Required">
        <span id="flavorid_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#flavorid_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Flavor<wbr>Id</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies the flavor ID. The options are as follows:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>modelarts.vm.cpu.2u</strong>: General-purpose Intel CPU specifications, suitable for data exploration and algorithm
discovery.</li>
<li><strong>modelarts.vm.cpu.8u</strong>: General computing-plus Intel CPU specifications, suitable for compute-intensive
applications.</li>
<li><strong>modelarts.bm.gpu.v100NV32</strong>: One NVIDIA V100 GPU with 32GB of memory, suitable for deep learning algorithm
training and debugging.</li>
<li><strong>modelarts.bm.d910.xlarge.1</strong>: One Ascend 910 NPU with 32GB of memory, suitable for deep learning code running
and debugging.</li>
<li><strong>modelarts.bm.d910.xlarge.2</strong>: Two Ascend 910 NPU with 32GB of memory, suitable for deep learning code running
and debugging.</li>
<li><strong>modelarts.bm.d910.xlarge.8</strong>: Eight Ascend 910 NPU with 32GB of memory, suitable for deep learning code running
and debugging.</li>
</ul>
</dd><dt class="property-required"
            title="Required">
        <span id="imageid_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#imageid_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Image<wbr>Id</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies the image ID of notebook.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-required"
            title="Required">
        <span id="volume_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#volume_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Volume</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type"><a href="#notebookvolume">Notebook<wbr>Volume<wbr>Args</a></span>

    <dd><p>Specifies the volume information. Structure is documented below.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="allowedaccessips_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#allowedaccessips_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Allowed<wbr>Access<wbr>Ips</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">List&lt;string&gt;</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies public IP addresses that are allowed for remote SSH access.

</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="description_csharp">

</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies the description of notebook. It contains a maximum of 512 characters and
cannot contain special characters <code>&amp;&lt;&gt;&quot;'/</code>.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional property-replacement"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="keypair_csharp">

</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>

</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="name_csharp">

        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>

    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies the flavor ID. The options are as follows:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>modelarts.vm.cpu.2u</strong>: General-purpose Intel CPU specifications, suitable for data exploration and algorithm
discovery.</li>
<li><strong>modelarts.vm.cpu.8u</strong>: General computing-plus Intel CPU specifications, suitable for compute-intensive
applications.</li>
<li><strong>modelarts.bm.gpu.v100NV32</strong>: One NVIDIA V100 GPU with 32GB of memory, suitable for deep learning algorithm
training and debugging.</li>
<li><strong>modelarts.bm.d910.xlarge.1</strong>: One Ascend 910 NPU with 32GB of memory, suitable for deep learning code running
and debugging.</li>
<li><strong>modelarts.bm.d910.xlarge.2</strong>: Two Ascend 910 NPU with 32GB of memory, suitable for deep learning code running
and debugging.</li>
<li><strong>modelarts.bm.d910.xlarge.8</strong>: Eight Ascend 910 NPU with 32GB of memory, suitable for deep learning code running
and debugging.</li>
</ul>
</dd><dt class="property-required"
            title="Required">
        <span id="imageid_yaml">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#imageid_yaml" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">image<wbr>Id</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">String</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies the image ID of notebook.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-required"
            title="Required">
        <span id="volume_yaml">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#volume_yaml" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">volume</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type"><a href="#notebookvolume">Property Map</a></span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies the volume information. Structure is documented below.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="allowedaccessips_yaml">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#allowedaccessips_yaml" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">allowed<wbr>Access<wbr>Ips</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">List&lt;String&gt;</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies public IP addresses that are allowed for remote SSH access.
If the parameter is not specified, all IP addresses will be allowed for remote SSH access.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="description_yaml">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#description_yaml" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">description</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">String</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies the description of notebook. It contains a maximum of 512 characters and
cannot contain special characters <code>&amp;&lt;&gt;&quot;'/</code>.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional property-replacement"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="keypair_yaml">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#keypair_yaml" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">key<wbr>Pair</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">String</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies the key pair name for remote SSH access.
Changing this parameter will create a new resource.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="name_yaml">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#name_yaml" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">name</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">String</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies the name of the notebook. The name consists of 1 to 64 characters,
starting with a letter. Only letters, digits and underscores (_) are allowed.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional property-replacement"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="poolid_yaml">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#poolid_yaml" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">pool<wbr>Id</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">String</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies the ID of Dedicated resource pool which the notebook used.
Changing this parameter will create a new resource.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional property-replacement"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="region_yaml">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#region_yaml" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">region</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">String</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>The region in which to create the resource. If omitted, the
provider-level region will be used. Changing this parameter will create a new resource.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional property-replacement"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="workspaceid_yaml">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#workspaceid_yaml" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">workspace<wbr>Id</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">String</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies the workspace ID which the notebook belongs to.
The default value is <code>0</code>. Changing this parameter will create a new resource.</p>
</dd></dl>
</pulumi-choosable>
</div>

<div>
<pulumi-choosable type="language" values="csharp">
<dl class="resources-properties"><dt class="property-required property-replacement"
            title="Required">
        <span id="type_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#type_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Type</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies the volume type. The options are as follows:</p>
<ul>
<li><em>EFS</em>: use Scalable File Service, default 50GB is <strong>free</strong>.</li>
<li><em>EVS</em>: use Elastic Volume Service, default size is 5 GB.</li>
</ul>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="mountpath_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#mountpath_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Mount<wbr>Path</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>The local mount path.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional property-replacement"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="ownership_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#ownership_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Ownership</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies the volume ownership. The options are as follows:</p>
<ul>
<li><em>MANAGED</em>: shared storage disk of the ModelArts service.</li>
<li><em>DEDICATED</em>: dedicated storage disk, only supported when the category is <code>EFS</code>.</li>
</ul>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="size_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#size_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Size</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">int</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies the volume size. Its value range is from 5 GB to 4096 GB.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional property-replacement"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="uri_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#uri_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Uri</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies the uri of dedicated storage disk, which is mandatory when the <code>type</code>
is <code>EFS</code> and the <code>ownership</code> is <code>DEDICATED</code>. Example: <code>192.168.0.1:/user-9sfdsdgdfgh5ea4d56871e75d6966aa274/mount/</code>.
Changing this parameter will create a new resource.</p>
</dd></dl>
</pulumi-choosable>
</div>

        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">int</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies the volume size. Its value range is from 5 GB to 4096 GB.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional property-replacement"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="uri_python">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#uri_python" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">uri</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">str</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies the uri of dedicated storage disk, which is mandatory when the <code>type</code>
is <code>EFS</code> and the <code>ownership</code> is <code>DEDICATED</code>. Example: <code>192.168.0.1:/user-9sfdsdgdfgh5ea4d56871e75d6966aa274/mount/</code>.
Changing this parameter will create a new resource.</p>
</dd></dl>
</pulumi-choosable>
</div>

<div>
<pulumi-choosable type="language" values="yaml">
<dl class="resources-properties"><dt class="property-required property-replacement"
            title="Required">
        <span id="type_yaml">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#type_yaml" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">type</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">String</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies the volume type. The options are as follows:</p>
<ul>
<li><em>EFS</em>: use Scalable File Service, default 50GB is <strong>free</strong>.</li>
<li><em>EVS</em>: use Elastic Volume Service, default size is 5 GB.</li>
</ul>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="mountpath_yaml">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#mountpath_yaml" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">mount<wbr>Path</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">String</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>The local mount path.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional property-replacement"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="ownership_yaml">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#ownership_yaml" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">ownership</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">String</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies the volume ownership. The options are as follows:</p>
<ul>
<li><em>MANAGED</em>: shared storage disk of the ModelArts service.</li>
<li><em>DEDICATED</em>: dedicated storage disk, only supported when the category is <code>EFS</code>.</li>
</ul>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="size_yaml">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#size_yaml" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">size</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">Number</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies the volume size. Its value range is from 5 GB to 4096 GB.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional property-replacement"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="uri_yaml">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#uri_yaml" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">uri</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">String</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies the uri of dedicated storage disk, which is mandatory when the <code>type</code>
is <code>EFS</code> and the <code>ownership</code> is <code>DEDICATED</code>. Example: <code>192.168.0.1:/user-9sfdsdgdfgh5ea4d56871e75d6966aa274/mount/</code>.
Changing this parameter will create a new resource.</p>

```sh
 $ pulumi import huaweicloud:ModelArts/notebook:Notebook test b11b407c-e604-4e8d-8bc4-92398320b847
```
